{"history":[{"role":"user","content":"What is the qualifying age for Age Pension?","timestamp":"2026-02-23T02:53:19.736Z"},{"role":"assistant","content":"The qualifying age for the Age Pension is 67 years. This applies to individuals born on or after 1 January 1957. For those born between 1 January 1954 and 30 June 1955, the qualifying age is 66 years, and for those born between 1 July 1955 and 31 December 1956, it is 66 years and 6 months. Individuals can lodge a claim up to 13 weeks before they reach their qualifying age [Source 1][Source 2][Source 3].","timestamp":"2026-02-23T02:53:19.736Z","sources":[{"index":1,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2023-10--aus140-2310nz.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/default/files/2023-10/aus140-2310nz.pdf","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.2809185133024971},{"index":2,"file":"pensions/who-can-get-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/who-can-get-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.3204292677621854},{"index":3,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2025-03--co029-2503.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/default/files/2025-03/co029-2503.pdf","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.34139589486458694},{"index":4,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2025-12--co029-2601.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/default/files/2025-12/co029-2601.pdf","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.3483262334859484},{"index":5,"file":"general/how-to-manage-your-age-pension-payment.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/how-to-manage-your-age-pension-payment","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.35266516228177247},{"index":6,"file":"general/how-to-prepare-to-claim-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/how-to-prepare-to-claim-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.3667594946021393},{"index":7,"file":"pensions/age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.37012529456669263},{"index":8,"file":"general/residence-rules-for-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/residence-rules-for-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.3764902235179144}],"memoryId":"mem-4c348898-1771815199736"},{"role":"user","content":"How does the income test work for Age Pension?","timestamp":"2026-02-23T02:57:52.436Z"},{"role":"assistant","content":"The income test for the Age Pension assesses both your income and your partner's income from all sources, including employment, savings, shares, and superannuation. The test determines how much Age Pension you may receive, as your income can reduce the amount of the pension paid to you.\n\nHere are the key points regarding the income test:\n\n1. **Income Sources**: All forms of income are considered, including:\n   - Deemed income from financial assets.\n   - Gross employment income (before tax).\n   - Net income from business activities.\n   - Family trust distributions or dividends from private company shares.\n\n2. **Free Area and Reduction**: There are income thresholds:\n   - For a single person, the free area is up to $218 per fortnight. If your income exceeds this amount, your pension will reduce by 50 cents for each dollar over $218.\n   - For couples, the thresholds are different, and the reduction rates vary based on whether they live together or apart due to ill health.\n\n3. **Reporting Obligations**: You must report any employment income you receive, but you do not need to provide payslips unless requested.\n\n4. **Special Considerations**: If you are permanently blind and receiving the Age Pension, the income test may not apply unless you are also receiving Rent Assistance or your partner is receiving a payment and is not blind [Source 1][Source 2][Source 3][Source 4]. \n\nThis income test is one of two tests (the other being the assets test) used to determine eligibility and payment rates for the Age Pension.","timestamp":"2026-02-23T02:57:52.436Z","sources":[{"index":1,"file":"payments/income-test-for-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/income-test-for-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.20743649967800323},{"index":2,"file":"pensions/who-can-get-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/who-can-get-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.230044962197656},{"index":3,"file":"payments/income-test-for-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/income-test-for-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.26837046034856255},{"index":4,"file":"pensions/who-can-get-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/who-can-get-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.2887935279850888},{"index":5,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2023-10--aus140-2310nz.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/default/files/2023-10/aus140-2310nz.pdf","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.2912609156239098},{"index":6,"file":"general/income-and-assets-tests-for-disability-support-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/income-and-assets-tests-for-disability-support-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.2998665046305649},{"index":7,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2025-03--co029-2503.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/default/files/2025-03/co029-2503.pdf","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.3115568155502299},{"index":8,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2025-12--co029-2601.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/default/files/2025-12/co029-2601.pdf","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.31651609955971693}],"memoryId":"mem-4c348898-1771815472436"},{"role":"user","content":"How long can I be overseas before my Age Pension is affected?","timestamp":"2026-02-23T05:07:18.468Z"},{"role":"assistant","content":"If you are receiving the Age Pension and plan to travel overseas, you need to be aware of the following rules regarding how long you can be away before your pension is affected:\n\n1. **Duration of Stay**: You can be outside Australia for up to 6 weeks without affecting your Age Pension. If you are away for more than 6 weeks, you must inform Services Australia.\n\n2. **Permanent or Long-Term Move**: If you are going to live in another country or will be away for an extended period, your Age Pension may be impacted, and you must notify Services Australia.\n\n3. **Reporting Requirements**: You must tell Services Australia if you are leaving Australia and any of the following apply:\n   - You are going to live in another country.\n   - You will be away for more than 6 weeks.\n   - You are receiving Age Pension under a social security agreement with another country.\n   - You are leaving Australia within 2 years after coming back to live and started receiving Age Pension since then.\n\n4. **Payment Adjustments**: If you are outside Australia for an extended period, your pension may be paid differently, and you must continue to meet the qualification rules at all times [Source 2][Source 3][Source 7].\n\nMake sure to keep Services Australia informed about your travel plans to ensure you receive the correct payment while you are away.","timestamp":"2026-02-23T05:07:18.468Z","sources":[{"index":1,"file":"general/residence-rules-for-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/residence-rules-for-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.3804269357976662},{"index":2,"file":"pensions/when-and-how-to-tell-us-about-overseas-travel-if-you-get-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/when-and-how-to-tell-us-about-overseas-travel-if-you-get-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.38588044420504725},{"index":3,"file":"pensions/travel-outside-australia-rules-for-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/travel-outside-australia-rules-for-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.40025154333383517},{"index":4,"file":"general/prepare-to-transfer-to-age-pension-if-you-get-disability-support-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/prepare-to-transfer-to-age-pension-if-you-get-disability-support-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.4080199629831518},{"index":5,"file":"general/how-to-prepare-to-claim-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/how-to-prepare-to-claim-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.417188980569854},{"index":6,"file":"pensions/travel-outside-australia-rules-for-pension-supplement.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/travel-outside-australia-rules-for-pension-supplement","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.41953928065575374},{"index":7,"file":"pensions/when-and-how-to-tell-us-about-overseas-travel-if-you-get-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/when-and-how-to-tell-us-about-overseas-travel-if-you-get-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.42020803508070176},{"index":8,"file":"general/how-to-manage-your-age-pension-payment.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/how-to-manage-your-age-pension-payment","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.4217142709116424}],"memoryId":"mem-4c348898-1771823238468"}],"memories":[{"id":"mem-4c348898-1771815199736","query":"What is the qualifying age for Age Pension?","answer":"The qualifying age for the Age Pension is 67 years. This applies to individuals born on or after 1 January 1957. For those born between 1 January 1954 and 30 June 1955, the qualifying age is 66 years, and for those born between 1 July 1955 and 31 December 1956, it is 66 years and 6 months. Individuals can lodge a claim up to 13 weeks before they reach their qualifying age [Source 1][Source 2][Source 3].","sources":[{"index":1,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2023-10--aus140-2310nz.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/default/files/2023-10/aus140-2310nz.pdf","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.2809185133024971},{"index":2,"file":"pensions/who-can-get-age-pension.