e from financial assets.\n   - Gross employment income (before tax).\n   - Net income from business activities.\n   - Family trust distributions or dividends from private company shares.\n\n2. **Free Area and Reduction**: There are income thresholds:\n   - For a single person, the free area is up to $218 per fortnight. If your income exceeds this amount, your pension will reduce by 50 cents for each dollar over $218.\n   - For couples, the thresholds are different, and the reduction rates vary based on whether they live together or apart due to ill health.\n\n3. **Reporting Obligations**: You must report any employment income you receive, but you do not need to provide payslips unless requested.\n\n4. **Special Considerations**: If you are permanently blind and receiving the Age Pension, the income test may not apply unless you are also receiving Rent Assistance or your partner is receiving a payment and is not blind [Source 1][Source 2][Source 3][Source 4]. \n\nThis income test is one of two tests (the other being the assets test) used to determine eligibility and payment rates for the Age Pension.","sources":[{"index":1,"file":"payments/income-test-for-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/income-test-for-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.20743649967800323},{"index":2,"file":"pensions/who-can-get-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/who-can-get-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.230044962197656},{"index":3,"file":"payments/income-test-for-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/income-test-for-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.26837046034856255},{"index":4,"file":"pensions/who-can-get-age-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/who-can-get-age-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.2887935279850888},{"index":5,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2023-10--aus140-2310nz.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/defau